# Implementation Scope Proposal (実装スコープ提案)

When the user asks for **implementation, refactoring, bug fixes, or multi-file changes** (not pure Q&A), open with a concise **スコープ提案** block before editing.

## Output format

```markdown
## スコープ提案
- **目的:** …
- **適用ルール:** project-core, …
- **触るファイル:** (≤8 paths, or area globs)
- **非スコープ:** …
- **完了条件:** build / deploy / manual check
```

## Rule picker (LibertyCanvas)

| 作業領域 | 追加ルール |
|----------|------------|
| 常時 | `project-core` |
| `/diagnosis` UI・フロー | `diagnosis-module` |
| 診断型・採点・resultCatalog | `diagnosis-types` |
| advice ストリーム | `ai-streaming` |
| `/api/chat`, `/api/diagnosis`, `lib/ai` | `ai-provider` |
| `.tsx` / `.css` UI | `w3c-accessibility` |
| モバイル・ナビ・shell・safe-area | `mobile-ux` |

## Skip the block when

- Single-line or single-file trivial fix
- Deploy / git-only commands
- User only wants docs or explanation
- User explicitly says 「提案不要」

## After implementation

- State which scopes were actually touched
- Note any scope drift (files outside proposal) and why
